{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775852872186,"sessionID":"ses_286ebe112ffeX3zH3bqYNGiKY6","part":{"id":"prt_d79144f0700151Sep11D6hVRKy","messageID":"msg_d791443ef0011SaeFS6v7yiWL1","sessionID":"ses_286ebe112ffeX3zH3bqYNGiKY6","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_c51d2b848c5444d89d72785d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/router/AR-010-session-management.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/router/AR-010-session-management.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Design: AR-010 — Router Session Management\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This document describes the technical implementation for session management capabilities within the Router module (`pkg/router`). The session management feature enables the router to track, manage, and enforce lifecycle policies for user sessions connecting to AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter backends.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Functional Requirements\n10: \n11: 1. **Session Creation**: Create a new session when a client makes the first request to a backend\n12: 2. **Session Tracking**: Track active sessions per backend (AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter)\n13: 3. **Session Binding**: Bind client requests to specific backend instances based on session affinity\n14: 4. **Session Timeout**: Enforce session timeout policies (idle timeout, max duration)\n15: 5. **Session Cleanup**: Clean up expired or abandoned sessions\n16: 6. **Session Metrics**: Expose metrics for active sessions, session creation rate, etc.\n17: \n18: ### Non-Functional Requirements\n19: \n20: 1. **Performance**: Session lookup overhead < 1ms p99\n21: 2. **Scalability**: Support 10,000+ concurrent sessions\n22: 3. **Reliability**: Session data persisted in Redis for recovery\n23: 4. **Thread Safety**: Safe concurrent access from multiple goroutines\n24: \n25: ## Architecture\n26: \n27: ### Component Structure\n28: \n29: ```\n30: pkg/router/\n31: ├── router.go                      # Main router implementation\n32: ├── router_test.go                 # Unit tests\n33: ├── handler.go                     # HTTP handler for proxy requests\n34: ├── handler_test.go                # Handler tests\n35: ├── resolver.go                    # Route resolution logic\n36: ├── resolver_test.go               # Resolver tests\n37: ├── health.go                      # Health check manager\n38: ├── health_test.go                 # Health check tests\n39: ├── config.go                      # Configuration structures\n40: ├── types.go                       # Type definitions\n41: ├── session/                       # NEW: Session management package\n42: │   ├── manager.go                 # Session manager implementation\n43: │   ├── manager_test.go            # Manager tests\n44: │   ├── session.go                 # Session data structure\n45: │   ├── session_test.go            # Session tests\n46: │   ├── store.go                   # Session storage interface\n47: │   ├── store_test.go              # Store tests\n48: │   ├── redis_store.go             # Redis-backed session store\n49: │   ├── redis_store_test.go        # Redis store tests\n50: │   ├── memory_store.go            # In-memory session store (dev/test)\n51: │   ├── memory_store_test.go       # Memory store tests\n52: │   └── config.go                  # Session configuration\n53: └── middleware/                    # NEW: HTTP middleware\n54:     ├── session_middleware.go      # Session extraction/attachment\n55:     ├── session_middleware_test.go # Middleware tests\n56:     └── auth_middleware.go         # Authentication middleware\n57: ```\n58: \n59: ### Integration Points\n60: \n61: - **Session Store**: Redis (production) or in-memory (dev/test) for session persistence\n62: - **Clientset**: Uses generated `versioned.Clientset` for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n63: - **Informers**: Watches `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` resources\n64: - **Existing Router**: Extends AR-009 router with session-aware routing\n65: \n66: ### High-Level Flow\n67: \n68: ```\n69: ┌─────────────┐\n70: │   Client    │\n71: └──────┬──────┘\n72:        │ HTTP Request (with/without session token)\n73:        ▼\n74: ┌─────────────────────────────────┐\n75: │   Session Middleware            │\n76: │   - Extract session token       │\n77: │   - Validate session            │\n78: │   - Attach to context           │\n79: └──────────────┬──────────────────┘\n80:                │\n81:                ▼\n82: ┌─────────────────────────────────┐\n83: │   Handler                       │\n84: │   - Check session affinity      │\n85: │   - Resolve backend             │\n86: └──────────────┬──────────────────┘\n87:                │\n88:                ▼\n89: ┌─────────────────────────────────┐\n90: │   Session Manager               │\n91: │   - Get/Create session          │\n92: │   - Update last activity        │\n93: │   - Bind to backend             │\n94: └──────────────┬──────────────────┘\n95:                │\n96:                ▼\n97: ┌─────────────────────────────────┐\n98: │   Resolver                      │\n99: │   - Look up route entry         │\n100: │   - Apply session affinity      │\n101: └──────────────┬──────────────────┘\n102:                │\n103:                ▼\n104: ┌─────────────────────────────────┐\n105: │   Backend (AgentRuntime/CI)     │\n106: │   - Proxy request               │\n107: └─────────────────────────────────┘\n108: ```\n109: \n110: ### Session Lifecycle\n111: \n112: ```\n113: ┌──────────────┐\n114: │   Created    │ (first request or explicit creation)\n115: └──────┬───────┘\n116:        │\n117:        ▼\n118: ┌──────────────┐\n119: │   Active     │ (requests being processed)\n120: └──────┬───────┘\n121:        │\n122:        ├─ Idle Timeout ──▶ ┌──────────────┐\n123:        │                   │   Expired    │\n124:        ├─ Max Duration ──▶ └──────┬───────┘\n125:        │                          │\n126:        ▼                          ▼\n127: ┌──────────────┐          ┌──────────────┐\n128: │  Terminated  │◀─────────│  Cleanup     │\n129: └──────────────┘  (delete) └──────────────┘\n130: ```\n131: \n132: ## Data Structures\n133: \n134: ### Session\n135: \n136: ```go\n137: type Session struct {\n138:     // Unique session identifier\n139:     ID string `json:\"id\"`\n140:     \n141:     // Namespace of the backend resource\n142:     Namespace string `json:\"namespace\"`\n143:     \n144:     // Backend kind: \"AgentRuntime\" or \"CodeInterpreter\"\n145:     Kind string `json:\"kind\"`\n146:     \n147:     // Name of the backend resource\n148:     BackendName string `json:\"backendName\"`\n149:     \n150:     // Backend URL for routing\n151:     BackendURL string `json:\"backendURL\"`\n152:     \n153:     // User identifier (from auth token or request header)\n154:     UserID string `json:\"userId\"`\n155:     \n156:     // Session creation time\n157:     CreatedAt time.Time `json:\"createdAt\"`\n158:     \n159:     // Last activity timestamp\n160:     LastActivityAt time.Time `json:\"lastActivityAt\"`\n161:     \n162:     // Session expiration time (CreatedAt + MaxDuration)\n163:     ExpiresAt time.Time `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n164:     \n165:     // Session state\n166:     State SessionState `json:\"state\"`\n167:     \n168:     // Metadata for extensibility\n169:     Metadata map[string]string `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n170:     \n171:     // Lock for concurrent access\n172:     mu sync.RWMutex\n173: }\n174: \n175: type SessionState string\n176: \n177: const (\n178:     SessionStateActive     SessionState = \"Active\"\n179:     SessionStateIdle       SessionState = \"Idle\"\n180:     SessionStateExpired    SessionState = \"Expired\"\n181:     SessionStateTerminated SessionState = \"Terminated\"\n182: )\n183: ```\n184: \n185: ### SessionConfig\n186: \n187: ```go\n188: type SessionConfig struct {\n189:     // Enable session management\n190:     Enabled bool\n191:     \n192:     // Session cookie name\n193:     CookieName string\n194:     \n195:     // Session cookie domain (optional)\n196:     CookieDomain string\n197:     \n198:     // Session cookie path\n199:     CookiePath string\n200:     \n201:     // Session cookie secure flag\n202:     CookieSecure bool\n203:     \n204:     // Session cookie HTTP-only flag\n205:     CookieHTTPOnly bool\n206:     \n207:     // Session cookie SameSite policy\n208:     CookieSameSite http.SameSite\n209:     \n210:     // Session token header name\n211:     TokenHeader string\n212:     \n213:     // Maximum session duration\n214:     MaxDuration time.Duration\n215:     \n216:     // Idle session timeout\n217:     IdleTimeout time.Duration\n218:     \n219:     // Session cleanup interval\n220:     CleanupInterval time.Duration\n221:     \n222:     // Store type: \"redis\" or \"memory\"\n223:     StoreType string\n224:     \n225:     // Redis configuration\n226:     Redis RedisSessionConfig\n227: }\n228: \n229: type RedisSessionConfig struct {\n230:     // Redis address\n231:     Addr string\n232:     \n233:     // Redis password\n234:     Password string\n235:     \n236:     // Redis database number\n237:     DB int\n238:     \n239:     // Session key prefix\n240:     KeyPrefix string\n241:     \n242:     // Connection pool size\n243:     PoolSize int\n244:     \n245:     // Connection timeout\n246:     DialTimeout time.Duration\n247:     \n248:     // Read timeout\n249:     ReadTimeout time.Duration\n250:     \n251:     // Write timeout\n252:     WriteTimeout time.Duration\n253: }\n254: ```\n255: \n256: ### SessionManager\n257: \n258: ```go\n259: type SessionManager struct {\n260:     config    *SessionConfig\n261:     store     SessionStore\n262:     metrics   *SessionMetrics\n263:     stopCh    chan struct{}\n264:     wg        sync.WaitGroup\n265:     mu        sync.RWMutex\n266: }\n267: \n268: type SessionStore interface {\n269:     // Get retrieves a session by ID\n270:     Get(ctx context.Context, id string) (*Session, error)\n271:     \n272:     // Set stores or updates a session\n273:     Set(ctx context.Context, session *Session) error\n274:     \n275:     // Delete removes a session\n276:     Delete(ctx context.Context, id string) error\n277:     \n278:     // List returns sessions matching namespace and kind\n279:     List(ctx context.Context, namespace, kind string) ([]*Session, error)\n280:     \n281:     // ListByUser returns sessions for a specific user\n282:     ListByUser(ctx context.Context, userID string) ([]*Session, error)\n283:     \n284:     // Close closes the store connection\n285:     Close() error\n286: }\n287: \n288: type SessionMetrics struct {\n289:     ActiveSessions   prometheus.Gauge\n290:     SessionsCreated  prometheus.Counter\n291:     SessionsExpired  prometheus.Counter\n292:     SessionsTerminated prometheus.Counter\n293:     SessionDuration  prometheus.Histogram\n294:     StoreLatency     prometheus.Histogram\n295: }\n296: ```\n297: \n298: ### SessionMiddleware\n299: \n300: ```go\n301: type SessionMiddleware struct {\n302:     manager *SessionManager\n303:     config  *SessionConfig\n304: }\n305: \n306: // ExtractSession extracts session from request\n307: func (m *SessionMiddleware) ExtractSession(r *http.Request) (string, error)\n308: \n309: // AttachSession attaches session to response\n310: func (m *SessionMiddleware) AttachSession(w http.ResponseWriter, session *Session)\n311: \n312: // WithSession wraps handler with session context\n313: func (m *SessionMiddleware) WithSession(next http.Handler) http.Handler\n314: ```\n315: \n316: ## API Contracts\n317: \n318: ### Session Token Format\n319: \n320: **Cookie-based (default):**\n321: ```\n322: Set-Cookie: agentcube_session=<session-id>; Path=/; HttpOnly; Secure; SameSite=Strict\n323: ```\n324: \n325: **Header-based (alternative):**\n326: ```\n327: X-AgentCube-Session: <session-id>\n328: ```\n329: \n330: **JWT Payload (optional, for auth integration):**\n331: ```json\n332: {\n333:   \"sub\": \"user-123\",\n334:   \"sid\": \"session-abc\",\n335:   \"nss\": \"default\",\n336:   \"bk\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n337:   \"bkn\": \"my-runtime\",\n338:   \"iat\": 1699000000,\n339:   \"exp\": 1699086400\n340: }\n341: ```\n342: \n343: ### Session Endpoints\n344: \n345: The router exposes management endpoints for session operations:\n346: \n347: ```\n348: GET    /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/sessions\n349:        - List all active sessions\n350:        - Query params: namespace, kind, userId\n351: \n352: GET    /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/sessions/{id}\n353:        - Get session details\n354: \n355: DELETE /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/sessions/{id}\n356:        - Terminate a session\n357: \n358: POST   /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/sessions\n359:        - Create a new session (explicit)\n360:        - Body: { \"namespace\", \"kind\", \"backendName\", \"userId\" }\n361: ```\n362: \n363: ### Session Management Interface\n364: \n365: ```go\n366: type SessionManagerInterface interface {\n367:     // CreateSession creates a new session\n368:     CreateSession(ctx context.Context, req *CreateSessionRequest) (*Session, error)\n369:     \n370:     // GetSession retrieves a session by ID\n371:     GetSession(ctx context.Context, id string) (*Session, error)\n372:     \n373:     // UpdateSession updates session metadata\n374:     UpdateSession(ctx context.Context, session *Session) error\n375:     \n376:     // DeleteSession terminates and removes a session\n377:     DeleteSession(ctx context.Context, id string) error\n378:     \n379:     // ListSessions returns sessions matching filters\n380:     ListSessions(ctx context.Context, filters *SessionFilters) ([]*Session, error)\n381:     \n382:     // CleanupExpiredSessions removes expired sessions\n383:     CleanupExpiredSessions(ctx context.Context) (int, error)\n384:     \n385:     // Start starts the session manager background tasks\n386:     Start(ctx context.Context) error\n387:     \n388:     // Shutdown gracefully stops the session manager\n389:     Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error\n390: }\n391: \n392: type CreateSessionRequest struct {\n393:     Namespace   string\n394:     Kind        string\n395:     BackendName string\n396:     BackendURL  string\n397:     UserID      string\n398:     Metadata    map[string]string\n399: }\n400: \n401: type SessionFilters struct {\n402:     Namespace string\n403:     Kind      string\n404:     UserID    string\n405:     State     SessionState\n406: }\n407: ```\n408: \n409: ### Resolve with Session Affinity\n410: \n411: **Modified Resolve Operation:**\n412: \n413: ```go\n414: // ResolveWithSession resolves route considering session affinity\n415: func (r *Resolver) ResolveWithSession(\n416:     ctx context.Context,\n417:     req *http.Request,\n418:     session *Session,\n419: ) (*RouteEntry, error)\n420: ```\n421: \n422: **Behavior:**\n423: 1. If session exists and is bound to a backend → return that backend\n424: 2. If session exists but backend is unhealthy → reassign to healthy backend\n425: 3. If no session → select backend using load balancing strategy\n426: 4. Update session's LastActivityAt timestamp\n427: \n428: ## Error Handling\n429: \n430: ### Error Types\n431: \n432: ```go\n433: var (\n434:     // Session errors\n435:     ErrSessionNotFound      = errors.New(\"session not found\")\n436:     ErrSessionExpired       = errors.New(\"session has expired\")\n437:     ErrSessionTerminated    = errors.New(\"session was terminated\")\n438:     ErrSessionCreateFailed  = errors.New(\"failed to create session\")\n439:     ErrSessionStoreError    = errors.New(\"session store error\")\n440:     \n441:     // Session affinity errors\n442:     ErrBackendUnavailable   = errors.New(\"backend unavailable for session\")\n443:     ErrAffinityBroken       = errors.New(\"session affinity cannot be maintained\")\n444:     \n445:     // Configuration errors\n446:     ErrInvalidSessionConfig = errors.New(\"invalid session configuration\")\n447:     ErrRedisConnectionFailed = errors.New(\"failed to connect to redis\")\n448: )\n449: ```\n450: \n451: ### Error Response Format\n452: \n453: ```go\n454: type SessionErrorResponse struct {\n455:     Error       string            `json:\"error\"`\n456:     Code        string            `json:\"code\"`\n457:     SessionID   string            `json:\"sessionId,omitempty\"`\n458:     Details     map[string]string `json:\"details,omitempty\"`\n459:     Timestamp   string            `json:\"timestamp\"`\n460: }\n461: \n462: // Error codes\n463: const (\n464:     ErrCodeSessionNotFound      = \"SESSION_NOT_FOUND\"\n465:     ErrCodeSessionExpired       = \"SESSION_EXPIRED\"\n466:     ErrCodeSessionTerminated    = \"SESSION_TERMINATED\"\n467:     ErrCodeBackendUnavailable   = \"BACKEND_UNAVAILABLE\"\n468:     ErrCodeAffinityBroken       = \"AFFINITY_BROKEN\"\n469: )\n470: ```\n471: \n472: ### Session Recovery Strategy\n473: \n474: | Scenario | Action |\n475: |----------|--------|\n476: | Session not found | Create new session, return 201 |\n477: | Session expired | Clean up, create new session |\n478: | Backend unhealthy | Reassign to healthy backend (if allowed) |\n479: | Redis connection lost | Fall back to memory store (if configured) |\n480: | Session store error | Log error, continue with degraded mode |\n481: \n482: ### Graceful Degradation\n483: \n484: ```go\n485: type FallbackStrategy string\n486: \n487: const (\n488:     FallbackMemory FallbackStrategy = \"memory\" // Use in-memory store\n489:     FallbackDirect FallbackStrategy = \"direct\" // Direct routing without sessions\n490:     FallbackReject FallbackStrategy = \"reject\" // Reject requests\n491: )\n492: ```\n493: \n494: ## Testing Strategy\n495: \n496: ### Unit Tests\n497: \n498: **File**: `session/manager_test.go`\n499: \n500: ```go\n501: func TestSessionManager_CreateSession(t *testing.T)\n502: func TestSessionManager_GetSession(t *testing.T)\n503: func TestSessionManager_DeleteSession(t *testing.T)\n504: func TestSessionManager_ListSessions(t *testing.T)\n505: func TestSessionManager_CleanupExpiredSessions(t *testing.T)\n506: func TestSessionManager_SessionAffinity(t *testing.T)\n507: func TestSessionManager_ConcurrentAccess(t *testing.T)\n508: ```\n509: \n510: **File**: `session/session_test.go`\n511: \n512: ```go\n513: func TestSession_IsExpired(t *testing.T)\n514: func TestSession_IsIdle(t *testing.T)\n515: func TestSession_UpdateActivity(t *testing.T)\n516: func TestSession_MarshalJSON(t *testing.T)\n517: func TestSession_ThreadSafety(t *testing.T)\n518: ```\n519: \n520: **File**: `session/redis_store_test.go`\n521: \n522: ```go\n523: func TestRedisStore_GetSet(t *testing.T)\n524: func TestRedisStore_Delete(t *testing.T)\n525: func TestRedisStore_List(t *testing.T)\n526: func TestRedisStore_ListByUser(t *testing.T)\n527: func TestRedisStore_ConnectionFailure(t *testing.T)\n528: func TestRedisStore_KeyExpiration(t *testing.T)\n529: ```\n530: \n531: **File**: `session/memory_store_test.go`\n532: \n533: ```go\n534: func TestMemoryStore_BasicOperations(t *testing.T)\n535: func TestMemoryStore_ListFiltering(t *testing.T)\n536: func TestMemoryStore_ConcurrentAccess(t *testing.T)\n537: func TestMemoryStore_MemoryLimit(t *testing.T)\n538: ```\n539: \n540: **File**: `middleware/session_middleware_test.go`\n541: \n542: ```go\n543: func TestSessionMiddleware_ExtractSession_Cookie(t *testing.T)\n544: func TestSessionMiddleware_ExtractSession_Header(t *testing.T)\n545: func TestSessionMiddleware_AttachSession(t *testing.T)\n546: func TestSessionMiddleware_WithSession_Success(t *testing.T)\n547: func TestSessionMiddleware_WithSession_InvalidToken(t *testing.T)\n548: ```\n549: \n550: ### Test Fixtures\n551: \n552: ```go\n553: func newTestSession(id, namespace, backendName, userID string) *Session {\n554:     return &Session{\n555:         ID:             id,\n556:         Namespace:      namespace,\n557:         Kind:           \"AgentRuntime\",\n558:         BackendName:    backendName,\n559:         BackendURL:     \"http://backend:8080\",\n560:         UserID:         userID,\n561:         CreatedAt:      time.Now(),\n562:         LastActivityAt: time.Now(),\n563:         ExpiresAt:      time.Now().Add(8 * time.Hour),\n564:         State:          SessionStateActive,\n565:     }\n566: }\n567: \n568: func newTestSessionConfig() *SessionConfig {\n569:     return &SessionConfig{\n570:         Enabled:         true,\n571:         CookieName:      \"agentcube_session\",\n572:         TokenHeader:     \"X-AgentCube-Session\",\n573:         MaxDuration:     8 * time.Hour,\n574:         IdleTimeout:     15 * time.Minute,\n575:         CleanupInterval: 1 * time.Minute,\n576:         StoreType:       \"memory\",\n577:     }\n578: }\n579: \n580: func newTestRedisConfig(addr, password string) *RedisSessionConfig {\n581:     return &RedisSessionConfig{\n582:         Addr:         addr,\n583:         Password:     password,\n584:         DB:           0,\n585:         KeyPrefix:    \"agentcube:session:\",\n586:         PoolSize:     10,\n587:         DialTimeout:  5 * time.Second,\n588:         ReadTimeout:  3 * time.Second,\n589:         WriteTimeout: 3 * time.Second,\n590:     }\n591: }\n592: ```\n593: \n594: ### Mock Setup\n595: \n596: ```go\n597: // Mock session store for testing\n598: type MockSessionStore struct {\n599:     sessions sync.Map\n600:     mu       sync.Mutex\n601: }\n602: \n603: func (m *MockSessionStore) Get(ctx context.Context, id string) (*Session, error) {\n604:     if v, ok := m.sessions.Load(id); ok {\n605:         return v.(*Session), nil\n606:     }\n607:     return nil, ErrSessionNotFound\n608: }\n609: \n610: func (m *MockSessionStore) Set(ctx context.Context, session *Session) error {\n611:     m.sessions.Store(session.ID, session)\n612:     return nil\n613: }\n614: \n615: // Mock Redis server for integration tests\n616: func newMockRedisServer() *miniredis.Miniredis {\n617:     mr, _ := miniredis.Run()\n618:     return mr\n619: }\n620: ```\n621: \n622: ### Integration Tests\n623: \n624: **File**: `session/session_integration_test.go`\n625: \n626: ```go\n627: // Test scenarios (requires Redis):\n628: func TestSessionManager_RedisPersistence(t *testing.T)\n629: func TestSessionManager_SessionExpiration(t *testing.T)\n630: func TestSessionManager_ConcurrentSessionAccess(t *testing.T)\n631: func TestSessionManager_CleanupRoutine(t *testing.T)\n632: func TestSessionManager_Failover(t *testing.T)\n633: ```\n634: \n635: ### Performance Tests\n636: \n637: ```go\n638: func BenchmarkSessionManager_CreateSession(b *testing.B)\n639: func BenchmarkSessionManager_GetSession(b *testing.B)\n640: func BenchmarkSessionStore_Redis(b *testing.B)\n641: func BenchmarkSessionStore_Memory(b *testing.B)\n642: ```\n643: \n644: ### Coverage Requirements\n645: \n646: - Session manager: 100%\n647: - Session store implementations: 100%\n648: - Middleware: 100%\n649: - Error handling paths: 100%\n650: - Overall: ≥85%\n651: \n652: ## Implementation Notes\n653: \n654: ### Session ID Generation\n655: \n656: ```go\n657: func GenerateSessionID() string {\n658:     // Format: sess_<timestamp>_<random>\n659:     // Example: sess_1699000000_abc123def456\n660:     return fmt.Sprintf(\"sess_%d_%s\", \n661:         time.Now().UnixNano(),\n662:         base64.RawURLEncoding.EncodeToString(randomBytes(16)),\n663:     )\n664: }\n665: ```\n666: \n667: ### Redis Key Schema\n668: \n669: ```\n670: # Session data (with TTL)\n671: agentcube:session:{session-id} = JSON(session)\n672: \n673: # User session index (Set)\n674: agentcube:user:{user-id}:sessions = {session-id-1, session-id-2, ...}\n675: \n676: # Backend session index (Set)\n677: agentcube:backend:{namespace}:{kind}:{name}:sessions = {session-id-1, ...}\n678: \n679: # Active sessions counter\n680: agentcube:stats:active_sessions = {count}\n681: ```\n682: \n683: ### Session Cleanup Strategy\n684: \n685: ```go\n686: // Background cleanup routine\n687: func (m *SessionManager) cleanupLoop(ctx context.Context) {\n688:     ticker := time.NewTicker(m.config.CleanupInterval)\n689:     defer ticker.Stop()\n690:     \n691:     for {\n692:         select {\n693:         case <-ctx.Done():\n694:             return\n695:         case <-ticker.C:\n696:             expired, err := m.CleanupExpiredSessions(ctx)\n697:             if err != nil {\n698:                 m.metrics.ErrorsTotal.Inc()\n699:             }\n700:             m.metrics.SessionsExpired.Add(float64(expired))\n701:         }\n702:     }\n703: }\n704: ```\n705: \n706: ### Session Affinity Algorithm\n707: \n708: ```go\n709: func (r *Resolver) resolveWithAffinity(\n710:     session *Session,\n711:     availableBackends []*RouteEntry,\n712: ) (*RouteEntry, error) {\n713:     // Priority 1: Session's current backend (if healthy)\n714:     if session != nil {\n715:         for _, backend := range availableBackends {\n716:             if backend.Name == session.BackendName && backend.Health.Healthy {\n717:                 return backend, nil\n718:             }\n719:         }\n720:         // Current backend unhealthy - need to reassign\n721:     }\n722:     \n723:     // Priority 2: Least loaded healthy backend\n724:     return selectLeastLoaded(availableBackends), nil\n725: }\n726: ```\n727: \n728: ### Connection Pool Configuration\n729: \n730: ```go\n731: func NewRedisPool(config *RedisSessionConfig) *redis.Client {\n732:     return redis.NewClient(&redis.Options{\n733:         Addr:         config.Addr,\n734:         Password:     config.Password,\n735:         DB:           config.DB,\n736:         PoolSize:     config.PoolSize,\n737:         MinIdleConns: config.PoolSize / 2,\n738:         MaxConnAge:   24 * time.Hour,\n739:         DialTimeout:  config.DialTimeout,\n740:         ReadTimeout:  config.ReadTimeout,\n741:         WriteTimeout: config.WriteTimeout,\n742:         OnConnect: func(ctx context.Context, cn *redis.Conn) error {\n743:             log.Printf(\"Redis connection established: %v\", cn)\n744:             return nil\n745:         },\n746:     })\n747: }\n748: ```\n749: \n750: ### Graceful Shutdown\n751: \n752: ```go\n753: func (m *SessionManager) Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error {\n754:     // 1. Stop cleanup loop\n755:     close(m.stopCh)\n756:     \n757:     // 2. Wait for background tasks\n758:     done := make(chan struct{})\n759:     go func() {\n760:         m.wg.Wait()\n761:         close(done)\n762:     }()\n763:     \n764:     select {\n765:     case <-done:\n766:         // Cleanup completed\n767:     case <-ctx.Done():\n768:         return ctx.Err()\n769:     case <-time.After(30 * time.Second):\n770:         return errors.New(\"shutdown timeout\")\n771:     }\n772:     \n773:     // 3. Persist in-memory sessions (if using memory store)\n774:     if ms, ok := m.store.(*MemoryStore); ok {\n775:         if err := ms.Persist(ctx); err != nil {\n776:             log.Printf(\"Failed to persist sessions: %v\", err)\n777:         }\n778:     }\n779:     \n780:     // 4. Close store connection\n781:     return m.store.Close()\n782: }\n783: ```\n784: \n785: ### Metrics Exposure\n786: \n787: ```go\n788: // Prometheus metrics\n789: func (m *SessionManager) RegisterMetrics(reg prometheus.Registerer) {\n790:     m.metrics.ActiveSessions = prometheus.NewGauge(prometheus.GaugeOpts{\n791:         Name: \"agentcube_router_active_sessions\",\n792:         Help: \"Number of active sessions\",\n793:     })\n794:     \n795:     m.metrics.SessionsCreated = prometheus.NewCounter(prometheus.CounterOpts{\n796:         Name: \"agentcube_router_sessions_created_total\",\n797:         Help: \"Total number of sessions created\",\n798:     })\n799:     \n800:     m.metrics.SessionDuration = prometheus.NewHistogram(prometheus.HistogramOpts{\n801:         Name:    \"agentcube_router_session_duration_seconds\",\n802:         Help:    \"Session duration in seconds\",\n803:         Buckets: prometheus.ExponentialBuckets(60, 2, 10),\n804:     })\n805:     \n806:     reg.MustRegister(\n807:         m.metrics.ActiveSessions,\n808:         m.metrics.SessionsCreated,\n809:         m.metrics.SessionsExpired,\n810:         m.metrics.SessionsTerminated,\n811:         m.metrics.SessionDuration,\n812:         m.metrics.StoreLatency,\n813:     )\n814: }\n815: ```\n816: \n817: ### Configuration Example\n818: \n819: ```yaml\n820: # Helm values.yaml\n821: router:\n822:   session:\n823:     enabled: true\n824:     cookieName: agentcube_session\n825:     maxDuration: 8h\n826:     idleTimeout: 15m\n827:     cleanupInterval: 1m\n828:     store:\n829:       type: redis\n830:       redis:\n831:         addr: redis.agentcube.svc.cluster.local:6379\n832:         password: \"\"\n833:         db: 0\n834:         keyPrefix: \"agentcube:session:\"\n835:         poolSize: 10\n836: ```\n837: \n838: ### Environment Variables\n839: \n840: ```bash\n841: AGENTCUBE_SESSION_ENABLED=true\n842: AGENTCUBE_SESSION_COOKIE_NAME=agentcube_session\n843: AGENTCUBE_SESSION_MAX_DURATION=8h\n844: AGENTCUBE_SESSION_IDLE_TIMEOUT=15m\n845: AGENTCUBE_SESSION_CLEANUP_INTERVAL=1m\n846: AGENTCUBE_SESSION_STORE_TYPE=redis\n847: AGENTCUBE_REDIS_ADDR=redis:6379\n848: AGENTCUBE_REDIS_PASSWORD=\n849: AGENTCUBE_REDIS_DB=0\n850: ```\n\n(End of file - total 850 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Design: AR-010 — Router Session Management\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation for session management capabilities within the Router module (`pkg/router`). The session management feature enables the router to track, manage, and enforce lifecycle policies for user sessions connecting to AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter backends.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Functional Requirements\n\n1. **Session Creation**: Create a new session when a client makes the first request to a backend\n2. **Session Tracking**: Track active sessions per backend (AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter)\n3. **Session Binding**: Bind client requests to specific backend instances based on session affinity\n4. **Session Timeout**: Enforce session timeout policies (idle timeout, max duration)\n5. **Session Cleanup**: Clean up expired or abandoned sessions\n6. **Session Metrics**: Expose metrics for active sessions, session creation rate, etc.\n\n### Non-Functional Requirements\n\n1. **Performance**: Session lookup overhead < 1ms p99","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/router/AR-010-session-management.md","time":{"start":1775852872127,"end":1775852872182}}}}
