{"type":"text","timestamp":1775852915017,"sessionID":"ses_286ebe112ffeX3zH3bqYNGiKY6","part":{"id":"prt_d7915060b001R6ARuIEU1mQ0YU","messageID":"msg_d7914fd420010O533hGlXyT70s","sessionID":"ses_286ebe112ffeX3zH3bqYNGiKY6","type":"text","text":"Now I have all the information needed to write a comprehensive tasks.md for AR-012. Let me create it based on the design spec and following the pattern from AR-010.","time":{"start":1775852915016,"end":1775852915016}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775853028169,"sessionID":"ses_286ebe112ffeX3zH3bqYNGiKY6","part":{"id":"prt_d7915094a001lerVIkIfq0uBvw","messageID":"msg_d7914fd420010O533hGlXyT70s","sessionID":"ses_286ebe112ffeX3zH3bqYNGiKY6","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_01236ed093c24fa5b3e6385b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-012/tasks.md","content":"# AR-012 — Session Storage Interface Definition Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-012 — Session Storage Interface Definition |\n| Module | `pkg/store` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n| Design Stage | ST-3 (Completed) |\n\n---\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Core Interface Definition\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `Store` interface in `pkg/store/store.go`\n  - Method: `Ping(ctx context.Context) error`\n  - Method: `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n  - Method: `StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error`\n  - Method: `UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error`\n  - Method: `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error`\n  - Method: `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n  - Method: `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n  - Method: `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error`\n  - Method: `Close() error`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-002**: Define `ErrNotFound` sentinel error in `pkg/store/store.go`\n  - Error message: `\"store: not found\"`\n  - Used when session key is absent on read\n  - Used when last-activity update targets missing session\n\n- [ ] **TASK-003**: Define key pattern constants in `pkg/store/store.go`\n  - `sessionPrefix = \"session:\"`\n  - `expiryIndexKey = \"session:expiry\"`\n  - `lastActivityIndexKey = \"session:last_activity\"`\n\n### Phase 2: Singleton Pattern\n\n- [ ] **TASK-010**: Create `pkg/store/singleton.go`\n  - Define `provider Store` package variable\n  - Define `initStoreOnce = &sync.Once{}`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `Storage()` function in `pkg/store/singleton.go`\n  - Calls `initStoreOnce.Do(initStore)`\n  - Returns `provider` instance\n  - Thread-safe singleton access\n\n- [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `initStore()` function in `pkg/store/singleton.go`\n  - Read `STORE_TYPE` environment variable (case-insensitive)\n  - Default to `\"redis\"` if unset\n  - Validate: only `\"redis\"` or `\"valkey\"` allowed\n  - Call `makeRedisOptions()` or `makeValkeyOptions()` based on type\n  - Construct Redis or Valkey store instance\n  - Log fatal via `klog.Fatalf(\"init store failed: %v\", err)` on error\n\n- [ ] **TASK-013**: Define provider type constants in `pkg/store/singleton.go`\n  - `redisStoreType = \"redis\"`\n  - `valkeyStoreType = \"valkey\"`\n\n### Phase 3: Redis Implementation\n\n- [ ] **TASK-020**: Create `pkg/store/store_redis.go`\n  - Define `redisStore` struct with fields:\n    - `cli *redisv9.Client` (from `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9`)\n    - `sessionPrefix string`\n    - `expiryIndexKey string`\n    - `lastActivityIndexKey string`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement `makeRedisOptions()` function\n  - Read `REDIS_ADDR` environment variable (required)\n  - Read `REDIS_PASSWORD` environment variable\n  - Read `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` (default `\"true\"`, case-insensitive compare to `\"false\"`)\n  - Return `*redisv9.Options` with `Addr` and `Password`\n  - Error if `REDIS_ADDR` empty or password required but empty\n\n- [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement `NewRedisStore()` constructor\n  - Takes `*redisv9.Options`\n  - Creates Redis client\n  - Returns `&redisStore{cli: client, sessionPrefix: \"...\", expiryIndexKey: \"...\", lastActivityIndexKey: \"...\"}`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-023**: Implement `redisStore.Ping()` method\n  - Execute `PING` command\n  - Expect string response `\"PONG\"`\n  - Return error if not PONG\n\n- [ ] **TASK-024**: Implement `redisStore.GetSandboxBySessionID()` method\n  - Construct key: `sessionPrefix + sessionID`\n  - Execute `GET` command\n  - If `redis.Nil` → return `ErrNotFound`\n  - Unmarshal JSON to `*types.SandboxInfo`\n  - Return error on unmarshal failure\n\n- [ ] **TASK-025**: Implement `redisStore.StoreSandbox()` method\n  - Validate: sandbox not nil, `ExpiresAt` not zero\n  - Construct session key\n  - Marshal sandbox to JSON\n  - Use Pipeline for atomic operations:\n    - `SETNX` session key with JSON\n    - `ZADD expiryIndexKey` with score=`ExpiresAt.Unix()`, member=sessionID\n    - `ZADD lastActivityIndexKey` with score=`time.Now().Unix()`, member=sessionID\n  - Execute pipeline\n  - Return error if any command fails\n\n- [ ] **TASK-026**: Implement `redisStore.UpdateSandbox()` method\n  - Construct session key\n  - Marshal sandbox to JSON\n  - Execute `SET key value XX` (key must exist)\n  - If key not exists → return error\n  - Do NOT modify ZSET entries\n\n- [ ] **TASK-027**: Implement `redisStore.DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` method\n  - Construct session key\n  - Use Pipeline for atomic operations:\n    - `DEL` session key\n    - `ZREM expiryIndexKey` member=sessionID\n    - `ZREM lastActivityIndexKey` member=sessionID\n  - Execute pipeline\n  - Return error on failure\n\n- [ ] **TASK-028**: Implement `redisStore.ListExpiredSandboxes()` method\n  - If `limit <= 0` → return `nil, nil`\n  - Execute `ZRANGEBYSCORE expiryIndexKey -inf before.Unix() LIMIT 0 limit`\n  - Get session IDs from result\n  - Pipeline `GET` for each session key\n  - Unmarshal JSON, skip missing keys (tolerate orphaned ZSET members)\n  - Return `[]*types.SandboxInfo`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-029**: Implement `redisStore.ListInactiveSandboxes()` method\n  - If `limit <= 0` → return `nil, nil`\n  - Execute `ZRANGEBYSCORE lastActivityIndexKey -inf before.Unix() LIMIT 0 limit`\n  - Get session IDs from result\n  - Pipeline `GET` for each session key\n  - Unmarshal JSON, skip missing keys\n  - Return `[]*types.SandboxInfo`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-030**: Implement `redisStore.UpdateSessionLastActivity()` method\n  - Validate: sessionID non-empty\n  - If `at` is zero time → use `time.Now()`\n  - Construct session key\n  - Execute `GET` to verify key exists\n  - If not exists → return `ErrNotFound`\n  - Execute `ZADD lastActivityIndexKey` with score=`at.Unix()`, member=sessionID\n  - Return error on failure\n\n- [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `redisStore.Close()` method\n  - Call `cli.Close()`\n  - Return error\n\n### Phase 4: Valkey Implementation\n\n- [ ] **TASK-040**: Create `pkg/store/store_valkey.go`\n  - Define `valkeyStore` struct with fields:\n    - `cli valkey.Client` (from `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`)\n    - `sessionPrefix string`\n    - `expiryIndexKey string`\n    - `lastActivityIndexKey string`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement `makeValkeyOptions()` function\n  - Read `VALKEY_ADDR` environment variable (required, comma-separated)\n  - Split by `,` → `InitAddress` slice\n  - Read `VALKEY_PASSWORD` environment variable\n  - Read `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` (default `\"true\"`)\n  - Read `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` (ParseBool, if true → `DisableCache=true`)\n  - Read `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` (ParseBool, if true → `ForceSingleClient=true`)\n  - Return `*valkey.ClientOption`\n  - Error if `VALKEY_ADDR` empty or password required but empty\n\n- [ ] **TASK-042**: Implement `NewValkeyStore()` constructor\n  - Takes `*valkey.ClientOption`\n  - Create Valkey client\n  - Returns `&valkeyStore{cli: client, ...}`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-043**: Implement `valkeyStore.Ping()` method\n  - Execute `B().Ping()`\n  - Expect string response `\"PONG\"`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-044**: Implement `valkeyStore.GetSandboxBySessionID()` method\n  - Construct key: `sessionPrefix + sessionID`\n  - Execute `B().Get().Key(key)`\n  - If `IsValkeyNil` → return `ErrNotFound`\n  - Unmarshal bytes to `*types.SandboxInfo`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-045**: Implement `valkeyStore.StoreSandbox()` method\n  - Validate: sandbox not nil, `ExpiresAt` not zero\n  - Construct session key\n  - Marshal sandbox to JSON\n  - Use `DoMulti` for atomic operations:\n    - `SETNX` session key with JSON\n    - `ZADD expiryIndexKey` with score, member\n    - `ZADD lastActivityIndexKey` with score, member\n  - Check all responses for errors\n\n- [ ] **TASK-046**: Implement `valkeyStore.UpdateSandbox()` method\n  - Construct session key\n  - Marshal sandbox to JSON\n  - Execute `SET key value XX`\n  - Success requires response `ToString() == \"OK\"`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-047**: Implement `valkeyStore.DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` method\n  - Construct session key\n  - Use `DoMulti`:\n    - `DEL` session key\n    - `ZREM expiryIndexKey` member\n    - `ZREM lastActivityIndexKey` member\n\n- [ ] **TASK-048**: Implement `valkeyStore.ListExpiredSandboxes()` method\n  - If `limit <= 0` → return `nil, nil`\n  - Execute `Zrangebyscore` with `Min(\"-inf\")`, `Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix()))`, `Limit(0, limit)`\n  - Get session IDs\n  - Use `Mget` to load all session keys (comment: keys should be in same slot)\n  - Unmarshal JSON, skip empty strings\n\n- [ ] **TASK-049**: Implement `valkeyStore.ListInactiveSandboxes()` method\n  - Same as `ListExpiredSandboxes` but on `lastActivityIndexKey`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-050**: Implement `valkeyStore.UpdateSessionLastActivity()` method\n  - Validate: sessionID non-empty\n  - If `at` is zero → use `time.Now()`\n  - Execute `Exists` key → must return 1\n  - If 0 → return `ErrNotFound`\n  - Execute `Zadd` with timestamp\n\n- [ ] **TASK-051**: Implement `valkeyStore.Close()` method\n  - Call `vs.cli.Close()`\n  - Return nil\n\n### Phase 5: Helper Functions\n\n- [ ] **TASK-060**: Implement `sessionKey(sessionID string)` helper\n  - Returns `sessionPrefix + sessionID`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-061**: Implement `marshalSandboxInfo(info *types.SandboxInfo)` helper\n  - Marshal to JSON string\n  - Return error on failure\n\n- [ ] **TASK-062**: Implement `unmarshalSandboxInfo(data string, info *types.SandboxInfo)` helper\n  - Unmarshal from JSON string\n  - Return error on failure\n\n### Phase 6: Testing (TDD)\n\n#### Unit Tests - Interface Contract\n\n- [ ] **TEST-001**: Create `pkg/store/store_test.go`\n  - Test `ErrNotFound` error message equals `\"store: not found\"`\n\n- [ ] **TEST-002**: Test `sessionKey()` function\n  - Given: sessionID `\"abc\"`\n  - When: `sessionKey(\"abc\")` called\n  - Then: returns `\"session:abc\"`\n\n- [ ] **TEST-003**: Test `marshalSandboxInfo()` with valid sandbox\n  - Given: valid `*types.SandboxInfo`\n  - When: marshaled\n  - Then: returns valid JSON string\n\n- [ ] **TEST-004**: Test `unmarshalSandboxInfo()` with valid JSON\n  - Given: valid JSON string\n  - When: unmarshaled\n  - Then: returns `*types.SandboxInfo` with correct fields\n\n- [ ] **TEST-005**: Test `unmarshalSandboxInfo()` with invalid JSON\n  - Given: invalid JSON string\n  - When: unmarshaled\n  - Then: returns error\n\n#### Unit Tests - Redis Implementation\n\n- [ ] **TEST-010**: Create `pkg/store/store_redis_test.go`\n  - Test `makeRedisOptions()` with all env vars set\n\n- [ ] **TEST-011**: Test `makeRedisOptions()` with missing `REDIS_ADDR`\n  - Given: `REDIS_ADDR` not set\n  - When: `makeRedisOptions()` called\n  - Then: returns error\n\n- [ ] **TEST-012**: Test `makeRedisOptions()` with password required but empty\n  - Given: `REDIS_PASSWORD` empty, `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` unset\n  - When: `makeRedisOptions()` called\n  - Then: returns error\n\n- [ ] **TEST-013**: Test `makeRedisOptions()` with `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`\n  - Given: `REDIS_PASSWORD` empty, `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=\"false\"`\n  - When: `makeRedisOptions()` called\n  - Then: returns options with empty password\n\n- [ ] **TEST-014**: Mock test `redisStore.Ping()` returns PONG\n  - Given: mocked Redis client returning PONG\n  - When: `Ping()` called\n  - Then: returns nil error\n\n- [ ] **TEST-015**: Mock test `redisStore.GetSandboxBySessionID()` with missing key\n  - Given: mocked Redis returning `redis.Nil`\n  - When: `GetSandboxBySessionID()` called\n  - Then: returns `ErrNotFound`\n\n- [ ] **TEST-016**: Mock test `redisStore.StoreSandbox()` with nil sandbox\n  - Given: `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)`\n  - When: called\n  - Then: returns error\n\n- [ ] **TEST-017**: Mock test `redisStore.StoreSandbox()` pipeline atomicity\n  - Given: valid sandbox\n  - When: `StoreSandbox()` called\n  - Then: SETNX, ZADD expiry, ZADD last_activity all called\n\n- [ ] **TEST-018**: Mock test `redisStore.UpdateSandbox()` with missing key\n  - Given: mocked Redis returning empty from SET XX\n  - When: `UpdateSandbox()` called\n  - Then: returns error\n\n- [ ] **TEST-019**: Mock test `redisStore.DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` pipeline\n  - Given: existing session\n  - When: `DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` called\n  - Then: DEL, ZREM expiry, ZREM last_activity all called\n\n- [ ] **TEST-020**: Mock test `redisStore.ListExpiredSandboxes()` with limit 0\n  - Given: `limit = 0`\n  - When: `ListExpiredSandboxes()` called\n  - Then: returns `nil, nil`\n\n- [ ] **TEST-021**: Mock test `redisStore.ListExpiredSandboxes()` tolerates orphaned keys\n  - Given: ZSET returns IDs but some GET return nil\n  - When: `ListExpiredSandboxes()` called\n  - Then: skips missing keys, returns found ones\n\n- [ ] **TEST-022**: Mock test `redisStore.UpdateSessionLastActivity()` with missing session\n  - Given: mocked Redis returning `redis.Nil` on GET\n  - When: `UpdateSessionLastActivity()` called\n  - Then: returns `ErrNotFound`\n\n- [ ] **TEST-023**: Mock test `redisStore.UpdateSessionLastActivity()` with zero time\n  - Given: `at = time.Time{}`\n  - When: `UpdateSessionLastActivity()` called\n  - Then: uses `time.Now()` for ZADD score\n\n#### Unit Tests - Valkey Implementation\n\n- [ ] **TEST-030**: Create `pkg/store/store_valkey_test.go`\n  - Test `makeValkeyOptions()` with all env vars set\n\n- [ ] **TEST-031**: Test `makeValkeyOptions()` with missing `VALKEY_ADDR`\n  - Given: `VALKEY_ADDR` not set\n  - When: `makeValkeyOptions()` called\n  - Then: returns error\n\n- [ ] **TEST-032**: Test `makeValkeyOptions()` with comma-separated addresses\n  - Given: `VALKEY_ADDR=\"addr1,addr2,addr3\"`\n  - When: `makeValkeyOptions()` called\n  - Then: `InitAddress = [\"addr1\", \"addr2\", \"addr3\"]`\n\n- [ ] **TEST-033**: Test `makeValkeyOptions()` with `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`\n  - Given: `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=\"true\"`\n  - When: `makeValkeyOptions()` called\n  - Then: `DisableCache=true`\n\n- [ ] **TEST-034**: Test `makeValkeyOptions()` with `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true`\n  - Given: `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=\"true\"`\n  - When: `makeValkeyOptions()` called\n  - Then: `ForceSingleClient=true`\n\n- [ ] **TEST-035**: Mock test `valkeyStore.Ping()` returns PONG\n\n- [ ] **TEST-036**: Mock test `valkeyStore.GetSandboxBySessionID()` with missing key\n  - Given: `IsValkeyNil` true\n  - When: `GetSandboxBySessionID()` called\n  - Then: returns `ErrNotFound`\n\n- [ ] **TEST-037**: Mock test `valkeyStore.StoreSandbox()` DoMulti atomicity\n\n- [ ] **TEST-038**: Mock test `valkeyStore.UpdateSandbox()` XX semantics\n  - Given: SET XX returns not \"OK\"\n  - When: `UpdateSandbox()` called\n  - Then: returns error\n\n- [ ] **TEST-039**: Mock test `valkeyStore.ListExpiredSandboxes()` MGET optimization\n\n- [ ] **TEST-040**: Mock test `valkeyStore.UpdateSessionLastActivity()` Exists check\n  - Given: Exists returns 0\n  - When: `UpdateSessionLastActivity()` called\n  - Then: returns `ErrNotFound`\n\n#### Unit Tests - Singleton\n\n- [ ] **TEST-050**: Create `pkg/store/singleton_test.go`\n  - Test `Storage()` returns same instance on multiple calls\n\n- [ ] **TEST-051**: Test `Storage()` thread safety\n  - Given: 100 goroutines calling `Storage()` concurrently\n  - When: all run\n  - Then: `initStore` executes exactly once, all get same instance\n\n- [ ] **TEST-052**: Test `initStore()` with `STORE_TYPE` unset\n  - Given: `STORE_TYPE` not set\n  - When: `initStore()` called\n  - Then: creates Redis store\n\n- [ ] **TEST-053**: Test `initStore()` with `STORE_TYPE=redis` (case-insensitive)\n  - Given: `STORE_TYPE=\"REDIS\"`\n  - When: `initStore()` called\n  - Then: creates Redis store\n\n- [ ] **TEST-054**: Test `initStore()` with `STORE_TYPE=valkey` (case-insensitive)\n  - Given: `STORE_TYPE=\"VALKEY\"`\n  - When: `initStore()` called\n  - Then: creates Valkey store\n\n- [ ] **TEST-055**: Test `initStore()` with invalid `STORE_TYPE`\n  - Given: `STORE_TYPE=\"invalid\"`\n  - When: `initStore()` called\n  - Then: logs fatal error\n\n#### Integration Tests - Redis\n\n- [ ] **TEST-060**: Create `pkg/store/store_redis_integration_test.go`\n  - Requires Docker Redis or testcontainers\n\n- [ ] **TEST-061**: Integration test `redisStore.Ping()` with real Redis\n\n- [ ] **TEST-062**: Integration test `redisStore.StoreSandbox()` → `GetSandboxBySessionID()`\n  - Store sandbox\n  - Retrieve by session ID\n  - Verify fields match\n\n- [ ] **TEST-063**: Integration test `redisStore.UpdateSandbox()` XX semantics\n  - Store sandbox\n  - Update sandbox\n  - Verify updated fields\n  - Try update non-existent → expect error\n\n- [ ] **TEST-064**: Integration test `redisStore.DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` cleanup\n  - Store sandbox\n  - Delete\n  - Verify GET returns `ErrNotFound`\n  - Verify ZSETs don't contain session ID\n\n- [ ] **TEST-065**: Integration test `redisStore.ListExpiredSandboxes()`\n  - Store multiple sandboxes with different expiry times\n  - Query with `before` time\n  - Verify correct sandboxes returned\n\n- [ ] **TEST-066**: Integration test `redisStore.ListInactiveSandboxes()`\n  - Store multiple sandboxes, update some with `UpdateSessionLastActivity`\n  - Query with `before` time\n  - Verify correct sandboxes returned\n\n- [ ] **TEST-067**: Integration test ZSET index consistency under concurrent operations\n  - Multiple goroutines Store/Delete concurrently\n  - Verify ZSET indices remain consistent\n\n#### Integration Tests - Valkey\n\n- [ ] **TEST-070**: Create `pkg/store/store_valkey_integration_test.go`\n  - Requires Docker Valkey or testcontainers\n\n- [ ] **TEST-071**: Integration test `valkeyStore.Ping()` with real Valkey\n\n- [ ] **TEST-072**: Integration test `valkeyStore.StoreSandbox()` → `GetSandboxBySessionID()`\n\n- [ ] **TEST-073**: Integration test `valkeyStore.DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` cleanup\n\n- [ ] **TEST-074**: Integration test `valkeyStore.ListExpiredSandboxes()`\n\n- [ ] **TEST-075**: Integration test `valkeyStore.ListInactiveSandboxes()`\n\n### Phase 7: Documentation\n\n- [ ] **DOC-001**: Add package documentation to `pkg/store/doc.go`\n  - Package overview\n  - Store interface contract\n  - Redis and Valkey backend support\n  - Singleton access pattern\n  - Configuration via environment variables\n\n- [ ] **DOC-002**: Add godoc comments to `Store` interface methods\n  - Document parameters and return values\n  - Document error conditions\n  - Include `ErrNotFound` semantics\n\n- [ ] **DOC-003**: Add godoc comments to `redisStore` methods\n  - Document Redis command patterns used\n  - Document pipeline atomicity\n\n- [ ] **DOC-004**: Add godoc comments to `valkeyStore` methods\n  - Document Valkey API patterns used\n  - Document DoMulti atomicity\n\n- [ ] **DOC-005**: Document key patterns in code comments\n  - `session:{id}` for JSON storage\n  - `session:expiry` ZSET for expiry index\n  - `session:last_activity` ZSET for activity index\n\n- [ ] **DOC-006**: Document ZSET score semantics\n  - Expiry score = `ExpiresAt.Unix()`\n  - Last activity score = `LastActivityAt.Unix()`\n\n- [ ] **DOC-007**: Document environment variables in `README.md` or code comments\n  - All `REDIS_*` variables\n  - All `VALKEY_*` variables\n  - `STORE_TYPE` selection\n  - Default values and required status\n\n- [ ] **DOC-008**: Add example usage in doc.go or example test\n  - Initialize store via `Storage()`\n  - Call `Ping()` to verify connectivity\n  - Call `StoreSandbox()` to persist sandbox\n  - Call `GetSandboxBySessionID()` to retrieve\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `Store` interface matches exact signatures from design spec\n- [ ] `ErrNotFound` error returned consistently for missing sessions\n- [ ] Redis implementation uses `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9`\n- [ ] Valkey implementation uses `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`\n- [ ] `Storage()` singleton initializes exactly once under concurrent access\n- [ ] Provider selection respects `STORE_TYPE` case-insensitivity\n- [ ] Default provider is `redis` when `STORE_TYPE` unset\n- [ ] Password-optional mode works for both backends\n- [ ] ZSET indices remain consistent after store/update/delete operations\n- [ ] `StoreSandbox()` uses pipeline/DoMulti for atomic index updates\n- [ ] `UpdateSandbox()` uses SET XX semantics (key must exist)\n- [ ] `DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` removes key and ZSET members atomically\n- [ ] `ListExpiredSandboxes()` uses ZRANGEBYSCORE on expiry index\n- [ ] `ListInactiveSandboxes()` uses ZRANGEBYSCORE on last_activity index\n- [ ] List methods tolerate orphaned ZSET members (skip missing keys)\n- [ ] `UpdateSessionLastActivity()` verifies key exists before ZADD\n- [ ] All environment variables documented and tested\n- [ ] All unit tests pass\n- [ ] Integration tests pass with real Redis and Valkey\n- [ ] Godoc documentation complete\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Source | Usage |\n|------------|--------|-------|\n| `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | External | Redis client library |\n| `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | External | Valkey client library |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | External | Structured logging |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | Internal | `SandboxInfo` type |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/types` | Internal | SandboxInfo alias source |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Order\n\n```\nTASK-001 → TASK-002 → TASK-003\n              ↓\nTASK-010 → TASK-011 → TASK-012 → TASK-013\n              ↓\nTASK-020 → TASK-021 → TASK-022 → TASK-023 → ... → TASK-031\n              ↓\nTASK-040 → TASK-041 → TASK-042 → TASK-043 → ... → TASK-051\n              ↓\nTASK-060 → TASK-061 → TASK-062\n              ↓\nTEST-001 → ... → TEST-075\n              ↓\nDOC-001 → ... → DOC-008\n```\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/agentruntime_reconciler.go\">\nERROR [166:12] undefined: json\n</diagnostics>","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/store/store.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":78,"character":8},"end":{"line":78,"character":38}},"severity":2,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://staticcheck.dev/docs/checks/#S1024"},"source":"S1024","message":"should use time.Until instead of t.Sub(time.Now())"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/go.mod":[{"range":{"start":{"line":17,"character":42},"end":{"line":17,"character":53}},"severity":2,"source":"go mod tidy","message":"github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2 should be direct"},{"range":{"start":{"line":39,"character":37},"end":{"line":39,"character":48}},"severity":2,"source":"go mod tidy","message":"github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5 should be direct"},{"range":{"start":{"line":78,"character":25},"end":{"line":78,"character":36}},"severity":2,"source":"go mod tidy","message":"gopkg.in/yaml.v3 should be direct"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/agentruntime_reconciler.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":165,"character":11},"end":{"line":165,"character":15}},"severity":